            "description": "Two-loop three-point triangle with a massless bubble insertion on one internal line, with two off-shell external legs $(p_1^2, p_2^2)$ and one massless propagator $x_5 = k_1^2$ promoted to a numerator/ISP. The 4xcut is computed in $d$ dimensions for arbitrary propagator powers, yielding 2F1 hypergeometric functions for the two canonical-basis integrals $I_1 = \\varepsilon R_{12} F_{11210}$ and $I_2 = (s F_{1221,-1} - \\varepsilon(p_1^2-p_2^2-s)/2 F_{11210})$. Results are expanded through $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^3)$ in the variables $x, y$ defined by $s = p_1^2 (1+x)(1+xy)$, $p_2^2 = p_1^2 x^2 y$, exhibiting uniform transcendentality.",
